Package: ClassEval
Type: Package
Title: Classification Methods and Evaluation Metrics
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Boqi", "Wang", email = "122090511@link.cuhk.edu.cn", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Yuyue", "Liu", email = "122090359@link.cuhk.edu.cn", role = "aut"),
    person("Ziqian", "Chen", email = "121040049@link.cuhk.edu.cn", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Provides a comprehensive suite of tools for classification tasks, 
    including implementation of support vector machines (SVM) and logistic 
    regression. The package offers robust evaluation metrics such as accuracy, 
    precision, recall, F1 score, and AUC. It features automated 
    visualization for ROC curves and confusion matrices, alongside utilities 
    for k-fold cross-validation and multi-model performance comparison. 
    While designed for general-purpose classification, it includes the 
    Titanic dataset as an illustrative example.
